title: Laura Michelle Hoskins (Federal Bureau of Investigation)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I would like to request any and all records on Laura Michelle Hoskins that you have. I would also like to request records if  my name is in the TSDI Watchlist and any others records to do with that as well. Ccfccf

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Laura Michelle Hoskins

title: Union Pacific Police Report - Yaeli Galdamez

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

First name: Yaeli
Middle name: Mozell
Last name: Galdamez
(Also went by alternate first name of Andrew. Also may have been known as Andrew Elijah Martinez)
Date of birth: 04/23/2000
Date of death: 09/04/2019
Place of death: Pomona, CA

This appears to have been a suicide death by train.
A reference news article is here:
https://imprintnews.org/featured/teens-suicide-brings-struggles-of-l-a-s-lgbtq-foster-youth-into-focus/37772

I have also included the medical examiner's report and the Pomona Police
department report for reference. The Pomona Police department record states
that their officer Solgat was handing the case to the Union Pacific police
department at the bottom of page 2 of the report. 

The Pomona PD Reference number is: P000224-082723.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Michael Laidlaw
